'''PLEX''', or Prairie Lindy Exchange, is an acronym used in various [[lindy exchange]]s in central North America. Historically, PLEXes are smaller than most lindy exchanges. Unlike most lindy exchanges, the hosting city may be different each successive PLEX.
PLEXes usually take place over a weekend. [[Lindy bombing]], live band dances, and a few workshops are typical events scheduled during an exchange. Rates are typically very inexpensive.
